Description: Streptococcus pneumoniae partial 23S rRNA gene, strain 547.
Organism : Streptococcus pneumoniae
Accession Number : AM180136.1

Streptococcus pneumoniae is a gram-positive bacterium. It is responsible for causing pneumococcal infections such as:
1. Community-acquired pneumonia
2. Bacterial meningitis.
3. Bacteremia.
4. Otitis media.
5. Sinusitis
6. Septic arthritis
7. Osteomyelitis
9. Peritonitis.
10. Endocarditis.
